1. PROJECT TITLE
Vehicle-to-Vehicle (V2V) Emergency Communication System

2. PROBLEM STATEMENT
In today's rapidly growing transportation environment, road accidents, vehicle breakdowns, natural disasters, and other emergencies often result in delayed communication between nearby vehicles. Traditional emergency communication methods rely heavily on centralized networks and human intervention, which may cause delays in delivering critical information.
Drivers frequently encounter unexpected road hazards such as accidents, theft incidents, fallen trees, roadblocks, animal crossings, and adverse weather conditions without receiving prior warnings. This lack of real-time communication increases the risk of secondary accidents and traffic congestion.
Therefore, there is a need for a Vehicle-to-Vehicle (V2V) Emergency Communication System that enables vehicles to directly exchange emergency alerts and safety information in real time. The proposed system aims to enhance road safety, improve situational awareness, and reduce emergency response times through instant communication between nearby vehicles.

3. PROJECT OBJECTIVES
Primary Objective
To develop a real-time Vehicle-to-Vehicle Emergency Communication System that enables direct communication of emergency alerts among nearby vehicles.

Secondary Objectives
Enable instant communication between vehicles.
Provide real-time emergency notifications.
Improve driver awareness and road safety.
Reduce accident response time.
Support GPS-based location sharing.
Maintain emergency alert history.
Provide a user-friendly interface.
Support multiple emergency categories.

